1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3002 By: Kendrix
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to counties and county officers;
amending 19 O.S. 2021, Section 130.1, as amended by
8 Section 1, Chapter 86, O.S.L. 2023 (19 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 130.1), which relates to the Commission
9 on County Government Personnel Education and
Training; extending sunset date; providing an
10 effective date; and declaring an emergency.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 19 O.S. 2021, Section 130.1, as
15 amended by Section 1, Chapter 86, O.S.L. 2023 (19 O.S. Supp. 2025,
16 Section 130.1), is amended to read as follows:
17 Section 130.1. There is hereby re-created, to continue until
18 July 1, 2026 2027, in accordance with the provisions of the Oklahoma
19 Sunset Law, the Commission on County Government Personnel Education
20 and Training, hereinafter called the "Commission". The Commission
21 shall be composed of the following five (5) members: The President
22 of Oklahoma State University or designee; the State Auditor and
23 Inspector or designee; the Director of the Department of
24 Transportation or designee; the Chairman of the Oklahoma Tax
Req. No. 15576 Page 1

1 Comm ission or designee; and the President of the Oklahoma County
2 Officers Association or designee.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
4 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
5 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
6 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
7 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
